OL,5,Clottery'
OL,7,FHazel Badjie, head of policy and
OL,8,Finfluencing in Wales for the National
OL,9,FDeaf Children's Society, said: "No
OL,10,Fchild with additional learning needs
OL,11,Fshould miss out on support because of
OL,12,Fwhere they live or go to school.
OL,14,F"It's crucial for schools and local
OL,15,Fauthorities to be fully equipped to
OL,16,Fsupport deaf children all through
OL,17,Ftheir education, if they are to
OL,18,Fprovide them with the best chances in
OL,19,Flife. But sadly, as the committee
OL,20,Fnotes in its reports, this is
OL,21,Fcurrently not the case.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                  G13/15
